Date of Birth: February 6, 1951<br/>
Birthplace: Salt Lake City, Utah, USA<br/>
<br/>
Born on February 6, 1951, Salt Lake City, Utah. He married Melanie Twitchell in 1973.
They are the parents of five children and have 22 grandchildren.
Attended the University of Utah. In 1995, Utah Valley University awarded him an honorary Doctorate of Business and Commerce.
In 1976 he joined Huntsman Container Company as sales representative, and in 1987, he was appointed President and Chief Operating Officer of Huntsman Chemical Corporation.
Elder Rasband was named a member of the First Quorum of the Seventy of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints on 1 April 2000.
He has served as a counselor in the Europe Central Area Presidency, president of the Utah Salt Lake City Area, executive director of the Temple Department;
and has supervised the North America West, Northwest, and three Utah areas as a member of the Presidency of the Seventy.
He had been serving as a member of the Presidency of the Seventy since 2005 and was serving as the senior president of the Presidency of the Seventy when called to the Twelve.
Elder Ronald A.Rasband was called to the Quorum of the Twelve Apostle on October 3, 2015.